---
title: Getting taken seriously as a software engineer.
date: "2018-05-21"
---
<p>I have found that while people assuming me to be smart when I tell them I am a software engineer,
it occasionally comes from someone who really only means "book smart". There is a perception of software engineers as being <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=software+engineer+socially+awkward&rlz=1C5CHFA_enUS726US727&oq=software+engineer+socially+awkward&aqs=chrome..69i57j0.8055j1j7&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8">socially awkward</a> and in many conversations with aspiring entrepreneurs, a lack of trust at your ability to understand the problem they are trying to solve or adeptness on anything outside of pure implementation will show.</p>
